                <p><b>Prep Time:</b> X minutes</p>
                <p><b>Cook Time:</b> 60 minutes</p>
                <p><b>Servings:</b> 3 cups <p>
            </div> 

            <div id="preparation">
                <h2>Preparation</h2>
                <h3>Equipment</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Pan</li>
                    <li>Stove</li>
                    <li>Food processor</li>

                    
                </ul>
                <h3>Ingredients</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Dried red lentils, rinsed, 1 cup</li>
                    <li>Water, 2 cups</li>
                    <li>Garlic, 1-2 medium-large cloves</li>
                    <li>Tahini, 3 1/2 - 4 Tbsp</li>
                    <li>Sea salt, 1 tsp</li>
                    <li>Ground coriander, 1 tsp</li>
                    <li>Lemon zest, 1/2-1 tsp</li>
                    <li>Paprika, 1/4 tsp</li>
                    <li>Red Wine Vinegar, 2 Tbsp</li>
                    <li>Lemon juice, 1 Tbsp</li>
                    
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div id="cooking">
                <h2>Cooking</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Place lentils and water in large sauce pan</li>
                    <li>Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to simmer and cover</li>
                    <li>Cook lentil until water is absorbed, about 20 minutes</li>
                    <li>Let lentils cool for 30 minutes</li>
                    <li>Add lentils and all other ingredients to food processor, puree until smooth</li>
                    <li>Enjoy now or let thicken in the refrigerator first</li>
                    
                    
                </ol>

            </div>

            <div id="notes">
                <h2>Notes & Tips</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Yum</li>
                    
                </ul>

